qas.question: Turkish cuisine originates from what source?
The cuisine of what territories are descended from Ottoman cuisine?
Turkish and Greek cuisine are descended from Ottoman Cuisine, along with the food of what other regions?

answers.text: Balkan cuisine, Armenian cuisine, and Middle Eastern cuisine

qas.question: Turkish coffee is descended from what?
Pita bread descends from what type of cuisine?

context: Much of the cuisine of <a1_0>former Ottoman territories<a1_0/> today is descended from <a0_0>a shared <a3_0><a4_0>Ottoman cuisine<a4_0/><a3_0/><a0_0/>, especially Turkish cuisine, and including Greek cuisine, <a2_0>Balkan cuisine, Armenian cuisine, and Middle Eastern cuisine<a2_0/>. Many common dishes in the region, descendants of the once-common Ottoman cuisine, include yogurt, döner kebab/gyro/shawarma, cacık/tzatziki, ayran, pita bread, feta cheese, baklava, lahmacun, moussaka, yuvarlak, köfte/keftés/kofta, börek/boureki, rakı/rakia/tsipouro/tsikoudia, meze, dolma, sarma, rice pilaf, Turkish coffee, sujuk, kashk, keşkek, manti, lavash, kanafeh, and more.
